<Q><L><HI>Cyrnus,</HI> I'll kindly teach tho&s;e Rules to Thee,</L>
<L>Which <HI>Good Men</HI> taught my un&s;iedg'd Infancy.</L>
<L>Be <HI>Wi&s;e,</HI> nor <HI>Pow'r,</HI> nor <HI>Wealth,</HI> nor <HI>Honour</HI> gain</L>
<L>From Deeds, who&s;e foul <HI>Inju&s;tice</HI> all will &s;tain.</L>
<L>Be careful next <HI>Ill Company</HI> to &s;hun,</L>
<L>But to a <HI>Good Mans Conver&s;e</HI> always run;</L>
<L><HI>Eat, Drink</HI> and <HI>Sit</HI> with him, and &s;till take care,</L>
<L>To make your <HI>Court</HI> to &s;uch, as <HI>Pow'rful</HI> are,</L>
<L>From <HI>Good Mens</HI> Conver&s;ation <HI>Good</HI> will flow,</L>
<L>Whil&s;t with the <HI>Ill</HI> you lo&s;e, what you already know.</L></Q></P>
<P>PROCEED we now, to take a view of the remaining Tokens of Antiquity and Zeal, which yet adorn the Modern State of lo&s;t <HI>Jeru|&s;alem.</HI></P>
